SCENE 1    "THE OFFICE"
-------
(Bill Gates is sitting in his office reading his employees reports)

BG = Bill Gates
EM = Employee

BG - Fools!! Windows97 won't be ready in time!
EM - But sir most programmers have taken their Christmas break.
BG - Ohh I hate Christmas, I hate presents, I hate people.
EM - What should I do sir?
BG - Recall ALL programmers now! If they don't finish the code they
     won't leave this place, ever.. Hahaha!


SCENE 2   "HOME"
-------
(Bill Gates has fallen asleep in his bed)

G = Ghost...

(Whop) = sound of spontaneous transportation

(A loud sound wakes Bill Gates, like a thousand souls in perpetual
torment, you know, the sound you make when installing Pee Cee
software and find you've run out of Hard Disk space before full
installation)

G  - I have come miserable one!
BG - What are you? What do you want from me? Do you know who I am?
G  - Ohh yes I know cursed one. You're the guy who tried to sell
     software at Paradise's accounting office. Do you know how much
     loss they've had? Damn you...
BG - It's not MY fault...
G  - Shut up! Tonight, three ghosts will visit you... They'll show you
     what an asshole you are... He he he,  Go to sleep now, you
     motherfucker. (Whop)

(Obviously, this is ONE hell of a ghost!).


SCENE 3  "THE GHOST OF CHRISTMAS PAST"
-------
(Bill Gates has fallen asleep again thinking it was only a dream.
Suddenly a cold limp pair of lips kiss him on the forehead and a camp
voice shouts in his ear).......

G  - Wakey wakey, its 12 o'clock you useless miserably stupid
     cretinous fuckwit nerd.         It's showtime..........
     The ghost had a hang up with the Film Beetleguse.
BG - Who are you? What are you? You look like a pansy, what do you
     want from me, a poor and honest housebuild. Erm, programmer?
G  - Programmer my sweet ass.  I'm the ghost of Christmas past and
     I'll take you on a journey to the past to see your Christmas
     many years ago.. Take my hand now sweetie pie before I start
     slapping your ass..
BG - Oh fuck!!!!!! (Whop)



SCENE 4 "TO THE SHOPS"
-------

(The ghost has transported Bill Gates to a computer shop at some past
Christmas and there's a huge crowd in the shop with lots of kids
buying stuff).

S  = Shop Keeper
FA = Father
KI = Kid

S  - So, what will it be?
KI - I want the Amstrad 6128 with a colour monitor..
FA - That's too expensive son, why don't you get the Spectrum?
KI - Or should we take the Commodore 64 which has lots of games?
BG - How foolish they were. Today that kid would be given a P150 with
     Windows and it wouldn't want anything else.
G  - And you think it would be happy? Fool. Look at how happy it is
     NOW, with a computer a thousand times smaller than the one you
     would have given him...
BG - I don't build computers, I only sell software.
G  - Smiling sweetly , Have a look at that miserable box over there..
S  - Of course, you can also buy this professional PC sir!
KI - No dad, I don't want it, it's no good..
G  - Smirking, Oh, how much! The kid knows!
FA - But it plays games, AND we'll also be able to run professional
     programs!
S  - And as Bill Gates said, "256K of Memory SHOULD be enough for
     everyone".
BG - Harumpfff.
G  - Hey sweet buns, have a look at that crowd of people over there..
BG - Hmm, they're at a.. A.. Ohh an Amiga.. My there going nuts over
     the games on that machine..
G  - (Whack! Whack!! Slapping Gates arse with a bag containing the
     lastest issue of Pee Cee help disks,..... The bag is very heavy).
     You stupid monkey, take a look at that miserable creature at the
     PC.
BG - With his back to the wall, Hmm, he's programming in Fortran using
     Ehem, edlin!
G  - What have you got to say about it?
BG - For it's time, it was...
G  - It was SHIT. As are Windows for their time.. But, it's time for
     me to leave you back at your house. Once he's finished with
     Saddam the second ghost will come over to show you Christmas in
     the present time....
BG - But I want to see how I was then..
G  - Sorry, honny bun, I'm in a hurry.. All I can say is that you were
     a slimy little nerd who liked to creat amateur programs with a
     "Professional" label.
     Are people so stupid after all? .. Byeeeee... (Whop)


                        --- Commercial Break ---

